{
  "logging": {
    "level": "INFO",
    "filepath": "bongo.log"
  },
  "leds": [
    {
      "row": 0,
      "col": 0,
      "type": "gpio",
      "pin": 12
    },
    {
      "row": 0,
      "col": 1,
      "type": "gpio",
      "pin": 13
    },
    {
      "row": 0,
      "col": 2,
      "type": "pca9685",
      "pin": 1,
      "address": 64
    }
  ]
}

Note: For a path like /var/log/bongo/, you may need to create the directory and set permissions first (sudo mkdir /var/log/bongo && sudo chown bongo:bongo /var/log/bongo). A simpler default for testing might be "filepath": "bongo.log", which will save it in the project root.